title: My Path
author: stefanie
text: let my heart be a rusty,  old token,  let life and death stand in my way,  i'll walk through crossroads bent and broken,  i'll stride the path i'm sent today.   for in life the roads are curvy,  and not all streets are neatly paved,  let me go all topsy-turvy,  i'll stride the path i'm sent today.   give me glory or give me pain,  sometimes i'll pass a speeding train,  and think of my life day by day,  i'll stride the path i'm sent today.   i'll stride my path again and again.

title: The Wedding
author: stephanie
text: as my sister and i,  stand on the grass next to the gazebo,  the warm june breeze running through my hair,  like a mom gently rocking her baby back and forth.   we stand nervously waiting for the justice of the peace to say the 6 most important words: ''who here gives this woman away?''  my palms are getting sweatier,  i can see it in my sister's eyes,  that she too,  is nervous.   i hear the music starting.   my mom gracefully walks on the grass towards us.   she looks as fragile as a vase,  arm in arm with my soon to be step-grandpa.   when she gets there,  the justice of the peace says the words.   tears are running down my sister's and my eyes.   we choke on our words.   ''we do''.

title: Family
author: stephanie
text: brother,  sister,  mother,  dad made up the family i once had  i wished them away,  and away they went all alone i sat and wept                   ***  mom wouldn't let me go to my best friend's party,   brother was just being a total smarty,  sister was being such a witch and when i told dad,  he said,  ''don't be a snitch''   i said they were horrible and stomped to my room,  i did not know that i'd soon be  gloomed i hollered out loud,  ''i wish you were gone!''  poof they left,  and i sang a happy song                     ***  later i got hungry and wished mom was here when a light bulb burned out,  it left me wanted dad to be near  i needed help on my math,  converting ounces to pounds  however,  my brother's helpful mathmatical brain was no where to be found my hair started to rad,  and this wasn't a new fad that's when i realized that my sister's criticism wasn't all that bad                    ***  now i'm homeless  and live on the streets alone i have no money,  no food,  no peeps  so when your family makes you mad,  just think of the family i once had  and do not wish them away - trust me,  life on the streets is sad!

text: what is love? love is kind with words.  love is genorous with friends and family.  love shows citizenship about giving teamwork.  love shows self control about recieveing discipline.  love never fails and never gives up.  love has a way of life of recieveing healing.  love shines in the sunset every night to show what god had made.  love is a gift from god.  love is tough for people in all kind of ways.  love gives us life and death to forgive.  how does love work? love is to share with other people.  love is in our lives forever even though we don't see it.  love is to show children that you care about them.  love shows spiritul fruit to other people and how they act and speak.  that is love and desire to speak truth from the bible and to people.  love is also how jesus died on the cross for our sins and how he got spitten at and talked bad about.  jesus will love us forever and ever.  this is what love is!

title: First Kiss
author: steven
text: i loved you ever sence i saw you,  i felt i sped into a dream and saw an angel.  6 years had gone and we were friends.  i couldn't tell you how much i loved you,  i felt the world would end.  i went to your house to do a project and we finished early.  we played truth or dare and you acted flirty.  your friend dared me to kiss you and you were shy.  i didn't want to either and then you caught my eye.   your blonde hair shined along with your eyes.  i reached over and kissed you. your cheeks were warm and rosy,  i wished it could never end but it did,  and it ended perfectly.  i ran outside into my grandpa's car and you gave me a pat on my back and smiled and laughed at the same time.  i still remember that day but every minute it slips into time.

title: Today I Saw A Rose
author: steven
text: today i saw a rose and wanted to give it to you so  beautiful were its pedals all covered in morning dew.   i carefully reached out  and picked it and carried it throughout the day holding it as i would you in a very special way.   i looked up to the heavens to ask god up above how i could send you this token of my precious love.   when no answer came a tear fell from my eye,  but i held onto that rose and looked back at the sky.   this time i'm not asking,  it's my praise i sent his way,  my thanks to him for you and this rose i held today.   for it was no easy task in which he had to do,  when he created such beauty,  this rose and especially you.

title: Lockdown
author: sylvia
text: lockdown it was a normal day.  at the end of second period,  everyone chatting contentedly  because for once our teacher let us have some free time.  then,  out of the blue,  came the announcement: â“this now begins the start of the run,  hide,  defend drill…. . â” but since our class was chatting,  we didnâ’t hear the drill part.  now after second period comes break,  but our teacher had not let us go yet.  she peeked in the adjoining classroom,  saw they were barricading,  and announced,  â“lockdown!â” there was a frenzy of activity,  because we all knew our roles: barricade the door with the bookshelves,  shove the tables together so they form a shelter,  reinforce the shelter so itâ’s ready,  then cower under the desks.  everyone was quiet,  scared.  we stayed like this for one excruciating minute.  then out of the pa system came the words,  â“that was the district-wide lockdown drill.  students,  proceed to your break. â” everyone was relieved for one moment before exploding in an angry chorus of  â“what!?â” and â“what !?â” it took 4 minutes of our 6 minute break to undo the lockdown because one of the bookshelvesâ’ shelf fell down.   dictionaries were strewn across the floor.  before our teacher told us to go to our next class.  poof! our break was gone.  and almost everyone was almost late to third period.

text: across the years he could recall his father one way best of all.  in the stillest hour of night the boy awakend to a light.  half in dreams,  he saw his sire with his great hands full of fire.  the man had struck a match to see if his son slept peacefully.  he held his hands each side the spark his love had kindled in the dark.  his two hands were curved apart in a semblance of a heart.  he wore,  it seemed to his small son a bare heart over his hidden one.  a heart that gave out such a glow no son awake could bare to know.  it showed a look apon his face too tender for the day to trace.  one instant,  it lit about and then the secret heart went out.

title: Baseball
author: tom
text: baseball is a sport of mine,  i would like to play it all the time.   when i am pitching on the mound,  i throw the ball with a grunting sound.  i make the ball go very fast,  and all teh batter can do is watch it past.   but when my pitch goes through the air,  and hits his bat and it goes fair,   my player's rush to get the ball,  but then i see eric,  my right fielder,  trip and fall.   eric gets up so quick and fast,  and grabs the ball and throws it,  as if his arm is in a cast.  the ball falls short and the runner keeps going,  just like the smooth,  mississippi flowing.   the ball is now rolling so close and near,  and jack,  the third baseman picks it up without fear.   he turns around and sees the runner,  and for the first time ever i saw him stutter.  but then his adrenaline kicks into gear,  and throws the ball home as quick as a white tailed dear.   i watch the ball go into todd the catcher's,  mitt,  and for that reason the coach didn't throw a fit.  he tags the runner,  and. . .  with all the fans in possible doubt,  they scream,  ''he's out! he's out!''  everyone looks at the ump,  and waits for his final shout,  he throws his arm up in the air and screams,  ''he's. . . out!''  the fans cheer loud,  and clap and roar,  for we won all the games in our season,  and shall play no more.   when next year comes,  we will start again,  and hopefully. . . our team can digest,  that possibly our team,  will not be the best.

title: Helen Keller
author: tracey
text: being deaf and blind sent helen kellerâ’s early childhood into rewind.  with the help of a person,  or a few,  helenâ’s life changed in an instant,  or two.  writing words in the palm of a childâ’s hand was all ann sullivanâ’s time seemed to demand.  at the age of seven helen began to learn what most children already understand.   helenâ’s education was beginning to bloom and the next years came and went so soon.  speech and writing entered helenâ’s world as her life at perkins school whirled around and around.  a new future at radcliffe was soon to be found classes were hard with no sight nor sound.   books to be published,  essays to be finished,  helenâ’s life seemed it would never diminish.  a leading role in a hollywood movie caught the eye of the media and local community.  the longing to travel brought new experiences for helen and ann to unravel  until the death of ann left helen baffled.   awards to accept,  public appearances to reject,  the next few years without ann would leave helen to alone comprehend,  what was the something that the past gave and the future would bring? soon helen realized,  life was either a daring adventure,  or nothing.

title: Meant to be

title: Beauty
author: vinitra
text: as a tranquil sun rises,  the mountains bow down their heads,  a vivid blue sky is lighted up,  that contrasts with bright red flowers like a red carpet  serving the feet of gentleness herself.   as the flowers raise their heads to the skies  their petals open gently,  as though hoping for a glimpse of heaven,  even though surrounded by thorns.  ah! irony,  such beauty in the midst of strife.

title: Being there ....

title: Mother
author: vinitra
text: a good mother as you can guess,  is not all that easy to possess,  she lives and works with love in her heart a glance from her pierces us like a dart,  our little unhappiness tears her to bits,  are we happy? then only she sits,  she not only cooks good foods she takes our sorrow and over that she broods dear mother i owe you a lot,  my love compared to your sacrifices is only a dot,  dear mom,  you protect me from peril,  you take care of me so much that i rarely fall ill,  i am grateful to you mother,  you are better than a sister or a brother.

title: ''Ice''
author: virginia
text: in the warming house,  children lace their skates,   bending,  choked,  over their thick jackets.   a franklin stove keeps the place so cozy  it's hard to imagine why anyone would leave,   clumping across the frozen beach to the river.   december's always the same at ware's cove,   the first sheer ice,  black,  then white  and deep until the city sends trucks of men  with wooden barriers to put up the boys'  hockey rink.  an hour of skating after school,   of trying wobbly figure-8's,  an hour  of distances moved backwards without falling,   thenâ—twilight,  the warming house steamy  with girls pulling on boots,  their chafed legs  aching.  outside,  the hockey players keep  playing,  slamming the round black puck  until it's dark,  until supper.  at night,   a shy girl comes to the cove with her father.   although there isn't music,  they glide  arm in arm onto the blurred surface together,   braced like dancers.  she thinks she'll never  be so happy,  for who else will find her graceful,   find her perfect,  skate with her  in circles outside the emptied rink forever?

text: eyes of sparkling blue fire  glare out at me from the dark like two chips of  expressionless ice.   mousy hair cut short and tipped with burning blond sprouts from the crown  and like deadly spikes,  juts forward,  gleaming  viciously with gel.   a thin mouth formed into an unemotional slash across a badly shaven face leers at me through the dark.  the pale lips pull back to  reveal teeth as formidable  as the red-eyed houndâ’s who prowls the graveyard smiling the same wolfish smile.   the icy eyes,  the blond tipped hair,  the thin mouth,  the wolf teeth all come for me.  my palms sweat.  my heart pounds.

title: Taco Bell
author: willow
text: i was driving one tuesday night,  in my new convertible-what a site.   my stomach was growling,   and my heart was pounding.    when suddenly i saw. . . the bell!  i started jumping in my seat,   i could not wait to eat! finally i pulled into the parking lot,   i got the very first parking spot.   i walked up to the door,   and i almost sank to the floor,     when i read a sign that said closed.     i slowly walked back to my car,   i had no taco bell after i had come so far.   as i pulled out i began to sing.    oh taco bell,   i will miss you so.   i will come back for you tomorrow.   it will put me out of my sorrow.   i will forever hear the ringing of your bell.

title: Can't Sprint
author: zach
text: my heart is pumping my mind is thumping muscles ready to run.   i'm waiting for the sound,   but my legs are stuck to the ground,  as i hear the gun.   i can't sprint off.  my legs are stuck to the block as everyone whizzes by.   i've lost my breath and can't think straight i'll be left in the wake of the runners,  i'm behind!  the race is over.  i walk off the track.  thinking i can't run with the pack but there is always next time.

title: I am a Jew
author: zach
text: i am a jew.  i wonder why we are hated and being killed.  i hear a whistle blow,  it is louder than a herd of startled elephants.  i see a land of wonders where everyone is free as the wind and there is no hate or death.  i want to be there in this place of wonders.  i am a jew.  i pretend that i am free in this magic land and all the nazis are in these camps in our place.  i feel their pleading presence begging to be let free like us,  but they are getting a taste of there own medicine.  i touch my bedroom wall that is rougher than sand paper made of jagged rock,  and i remember that this is only a fantasy.  i worry that i will be the next person to die in this vile place called a concentration camp.  i cry when yet another person is being led away to his death.  my tears run down my face like a waterfall that never runs dry.  i remember my old life before the holocaust and cry harder because that was when we were free and i was allowed to choose my own clothing,  and draw in my favorite notebook which i was forced to leave behind.  that was then.  this is now.  i am a jew.  i understand that the nazis hate us,  but i do not know why.  i say we will be rescued eventually,  but no one hears me.  it is all i can do not to run out the door and scream and hit every single nazi i see,  but i know i would be killed,  and my dream would never come true.  i dream that we,  all of us,  will be in that place that i imagine every single day and night.  i try to get there but,  alas,  it is only a fantasy.  i hope that one day soon that dream will become a reality.  we will be free.  i am a jew.  that is why this is happening to me.  i hear a gunshot that breaks the silence.  its sound is louder than a clap of thunder.  i hear the cries of pain,  but by now they are stifled.  they are coming from outside.  i look out the window and immediately grimaced and feel sick like a person who had just eaten a hundred worms in rotten bread the body of the woman i had just heard was right outside the window.  the nazi who had shot her is smiling and cackling maniacally.  his eyes look dark and merciless.  i did not know the woman,  but i knew she was new to here.  she did not expect anything.  a torah was on the ground near her.  she must have not known we were not allowed to practice our religion here.  she died so fast.  i am a jew.  that is why this is happening to us.  god save us.  save our souls.

title: The Battle
author: zach
text: in the barren field   loomed malignant orcs.  they chose not to yield   and were demolished like corks.   the hostile foe was obscured in the wood   but the men knew how to act.  they inflicted pain where they could   then came elves,  with whom they had a pact.   the elves were animated   as bow strings were released.  the foe was concentrated   and most ended deceased.   the orcs were advancing   as gunshots fired.  the technology was enhancing   and spirits were hired.   the men fought the orcs hand-to-hand   they hit them hard.  it was a fight for the land   and the foe shattered like a shard.   the men held off the orc attack   but they knew the enemy would come back.

title: Love in hate and joy
author: zack
text: some say love is a breeze that lifts your spirit.   others say love is a razor that leaves your heart to bleed.  that blood flows though the stream of tears and taints the waters of joy.  that sadness seeps down to the soul and soon becomes hate.  that hate poisons the mind and soul,  and love is unattainable.  but shared love can only make you strong.    your spirits will sour above the clouds in a beautiful symphony.  you are both reborn as one.  tears,  sorrow,  laughter,  and joy are all shared by two souls .

title: The Death of my cousin
author: zhyaisha
text: the death of my cousin was very hurtful to me and my family,   somebody please tell me why she had to leave me.   if only she was still here i would probably be with her right now,   i guess all i have to do is sit back and take a bow.   when my cousin died all her sister was worried about was getting her hair and nails done,   she was only nineteen and she couldn't even have a son.   the boy that killed my cousin name is shakim,   if only he was not in jail i would probably try to kill him.   they only gave him five years in jail and one year on probation and that not fair because they gave my cousin dell her brother the same amout of time because they said that he was the one who killed his own sister,   but no matter what nobody say i will still miss her.   there is nothing that i can do now because she is gone and i cant bring her back from the dead,   and all i had to sit there and do was watch my cousin lay there on her death bed.   if only i could bring her back we would have a good time,   and maybe if i needed some money she would give me a dime.   the person that i am talking about in this poem name is lakia ''ke-ke''jones the person that used to always call zhyaisha r.  her baby,   she was the best cousin that anybody could ever have to me.   i have one more last thing to say before i go. . . . .         i love you lakia''ke-ke''jones \t\t      r. i. p.  big cuz  \t\t\t\t  1-love

text: i have a wall you cannot see,  because itâ’s deep inside of me.  it blocks my heart on every side,  and helps emotions there to hide.  you canâ’t reach in,  i canâ’t reach out.  you wonder what itâ’s all about.   the wall i built that you cannot see,  results from insecurity.  each time my tender heart was hurt,  the stairs within grew worse and worse.  so stone by stone,  i built a wall thatâ’s now so thick it will not fall.   please understand that itâ’s not you.  continue trying to break through.  i want so much to show myself,  and love from you will really help.  so bit by bit,  chip my wall,  till stone by stone,  it begins to fall.   i know the process will be slow,  itâ’s never easy to let go,  of hurts and failures long ingrained upon ones heart from years of pain.  iâ’m so afraid to let you in,  i know i might get hurt again.   i try so hard to break the wall,  but seem to get nowhere at all.  for stone upon each stone iâ’ve stacked; and left between them not a crack,  the only way to make it fall,  is imperfections in the wall.   i did the best i could to build a perfect wall,  but there is still a few small flaws-which are the key-to breaking through the wall to me.  please use each flaw to cause a crack.  to knock a stone off the stack.   for just as stone by stone was laid,  with every hurt,  with every pain.  so stone by stone the wall will break.  as love replaces every ache,  please be the one who cares enough,  to find the flaws,  no matter what.

title: Strength
author: aaron
text: staring at the walls,  glaring at the clock,  growing ever furious,  with each tick,  with each tock.   determination,  as the minutes fly by,  i know what has to be done.  yet,  why even try?  you are my weakness,  although i am strong.  i just canâ’t help feeling,  how is it right,  when it is so wrong?  even when we fight,  deep down i know,  it doesnâ’t take strength to hold on,  it takes strength to let go.

title: Changes
author: aaron
text: â“friends forever, â” you promised â“together till the end. â” we did everything with each other you were my best friend  when i was sad,  you were by my side when i was scared,  you felt my fear you were my best support- if i needed you,  you were there  you were the greatest friend,  you always knew what to say: you made everything seem better.  as long as we had each other,  everything would be okay.   but somewhere along the line,  we slowly came apart.  i was here,  you were there it tore a hole in my heart.   things were changing,  our cheerful music reversed its tune.  it was like having salt without pepper,  a sun without a moon.   suddenly,  we were miles apart.  two different people,  with nothing the same.  it was as if we hadnâ’t been friends; although we knew deep in our hearts,  neither one of us was to blame.   you had made many new friends,  and luckily,  so had i,  but that didnâ’t change the hurt- the loss of our friendship made me cry.   as we grow older,  things must change,  but they donâ’t always have to end.  even though it is different now,  you will always be my friend.

title: Children's Eyes
author: aaron
text: what kind of world is it,  my friend,  that little children see? i wonder if they see god first because they just believe?  do they see strength in caring eyes who watch them as they play,  or maybe love through gentle hands that guide them on their way?  do you think they dream of future times when they would be king or queen,  or just enjoy their present life while with their friends they sing?  do they see the acts of kindness done for people who are poor? is the very best in everyone what they are looking for?  and when the day is over,  as they close their eyes to sleep,  do they look forward to tomorrow with its promises to keep?  if this is what the children see,  then it should be no surprise,  the world would be a better place if we all had childrenâ’s eyes.

title: Enough
author: aaron
text: her words slapped my skin.  thick tears poured down my cheeks.  the bite of her tone shot venom through my veins.  the room was a cell,  a tomb,  with my pain echoing in the silence that surrounded us.  staring into her dark eyes was like staring into the barrel of a gun,  loaded with what could be the end of me.  i listened as she listed my flaws that had already turned me into the hunched over figure that i had become.  my shattered trust lay on the icy floor and i hoped that she didnâ’t cut her feet on her way out.

title: Dark Eyes
author: abby
text: well,  hello,  young man! my,  what dark eyes you have,  dark enough,  oh yes,  dark enough indeed.  they must catch a woman's stare,  oh they must! you look right into them,  into their very soul.  and yet. . .  they do not.  they are but innocent eyes,  dark yes,  but innocent.  oh,  how they must perplex the women's minds,  indeed! but,  how can i see them through the locks of your hair? your hair! oh,  my,  sir! never have i seen such hair on a man such a you before! begging your pardon how blond it is! and unusual,  too just the right length,  of course on anyone else,  why,  they'd look like a girl but on you! my! quite handome!  i do not know of many women who deserve to look upon a face so sweet and pure! in fact,  i only know but one:  her body is nothing special,  she's quite normal,  to be honest. . .  but when you look at the details,  my,  oh,  my,  she can be beautiful.   oh,  her hair you must see her hair! blond as blond can get,  almost white,  sometimes. . .  flowing down down down down down.  why,  it is so long it doesn't seem to stop!  heavens,  that is but the least of it!  her eyes are the best part; quite like yours.  dark as the sea on a stormy night,  and light as a cloudless sky.  it changes constantly,  quite strange,  really.  a jagged line cuts through it,  circular,  all the way around one part dark;  one part light; never,  never just one color.  never constant,   forever changing,  always beautiful.   why yes,  now i think of it,  sir  (if it not be prude)  you must see her,  oh you must! your features make the perfect match!  take a chance,  go on! do not live you life waiting for women to come to you you will just live your life alone,   take it from someone who knows (me)  look! oh look at the way she stares at you with those most sursprising eyes.  they are quite unique,  are they not? no one will ever have eyes much like hers. . .   go ahead,  young man! do not end up like me! although this is not a fairy tale:  that doesn't mean it can't end like one!

title: A Soldier Never Stops
author: aleigh
text: sadness.  happiness.  strength.   love.    a soldier never stops,  he never gives up.   fighting for peace,  hope and family.    a soldier never stops,  thinking about his family,  as he sits there alone.   he never once forgets,  the prize of it all.    a soldier never stops,  supporting his nation,  his troops  and the path of life he has chosen.   a soldier never stops,   firing that gun,  knowing that he may die,  but takes his chances  anyway.    a soldier never stops,  to think that war is stupid,  worthless or a waste of time,  but to think that family is home and that's.  thatâ’s what he is waiting for.    a soldier never stops,  planning his next move,  he never wastes his time,  he admires the time he has.   as you sit at home worrying,  is he alive?  will he come home? does he think about me everyday.    as you sit at home,  those men and women are fighting,  for peace,  harmony,  family,  and love.    to think that a soldier never stops,  praying for you,  thinking of you,  itâ’s all  for you.

title: Forgive My Mistake
author: alison
text: not always sure what things called sins may be,   i am sure of one sin i have done.  it was several years ago,  and i was a fawn,  i stood in the field of grass with my friend,  the school stood lifeless and lonely.  the companion chirping with happiness,  not a wisp of hair in her mind,  knew what was going to happen.   i raised my chin,  standing tall,  staring at the culprit of my hand.  my palm met her cheek with great force,  the body crashing to the ground like a sunken ship.  i flew away,  long afar,  waiting for a girl to come laughing back,  coming back,  a doe frolicking and dancing.  but she turned and cried,   a violin of tears,  swimming out of her weeping.  watching her leave,   her wretched heart bleeding thorns,  each needle pulling another tear from her empty,  innocent body.    for weeks i heard her when i walked to school,   the depressing notes of string,  walking by me,  when sheâ’s never really there.  with her torn-up heart,  flying weakly,  never to recover again.   i try to think of happy things,  yet the violin of despair,  always makes it through to the mind of regret.  time cannot erase this shame,  with the golden hair of the girl caught in the forever trap of pain.  eternally i hope and want,  all girls and friends of mine,  so kind and compassionate will forgive my mistake.

title: From The Dark Comes A Light

title: Going back to space, still coming back alone
author: alyss
text: going back to space,  still coming abck alone.   i went back to space and tryed again  to find myself.   when i was out there,  i thought i found myself,  but i'm not sure.   going back to space,  still coming back alone.   i am back and my body are the stars and planets.   people now know  where i've been,  but now ask why and what was i doing.   i still do not answer,  ''i ran away and decided to come back. ''  going to space,  still coming back alone.   they look into my eyes and they still run away.   i wonde why,  i look into a mirror and i see  that my eyes are forever cold and dark.  and now they filled  are filled with hatred.   the cold.  dark hatred eyes are now th new me.   going back to space,  still coming back alone.   i have no one to love, or to care for.   i never will.   going back to space,  still coming back alone.   my arm is grabbed   i am turned around,  and now  i face soft,  sea green eyes.   the soft,  sea green eyes look into the now forever cold,  dark,  hatred eyes that are me.   now i do have someone to love and care for.   i was wrong.   going back to space,  still coming back al;one.   my eyes soften,  but the stars and planets are still my body.   and the man with the soft,  sea green eyes; his body becomes the  stars and planets too.   we go off back to space never to return to earth.   going back to space,  and now not alone.

title: My Peace of Mind
author: amanda
text: flipping through photos of you so slowly,  sitting beneath a tree.  i think about how you have always been my  peace of mind.   i will slip into the sun,  letting my face turn gold,   feeling the warmth,  and tasting the sun.  and i will. . . . .   let the wind just caress my face,  or let it gather me up and take me away.   i float on the wind,  and sleep on the clouds,   in a peace of mind.    but if i should fall,  my emotions to tangled,   i shall fall with pride in my soul.   for i know you will be there to catch me,   to cradle me,  to stitch up my heart.    your're my dream catcher,  my blueberry patch,  my ever ever after.  my peace to my peace of mind.     when you put me down i will slip into the sun again,  with you and a patched up blanket.   and sit and let the grass smell fill my nose,  and let the world just pass us by.    i will look into your hunny eyes,   amazed at how the sunlight makes the drops of blue dance and twinkle.   my own personal milky way,  and my  mind will go numb,  as my eyes hold youyr gaze,  and you will catipolt me back into my peace of mind.   and i will. . . . . .   let the wind just carass my face,   or let it gather me up and take me away.   i float on the wind,  and sleep on the clouds,  in a peace of mind.    but if i should fall,  my emotions to tangled,  i shall fall with pride in my soul.   for i know you will be there to catch me,   to cradle me,  to stitch up my heart.    your my dream catcher,  my blueberry patch,  by ever ever after,   your my peace to my peace of mind.    as long as you're with me,  there will be peace.   peace in my peace of mind.

title: Mike
author: amber
text: mike is so sweet! he's cute,  nice,  funny,  and kind.   he is so lovable.  crazy and beautiful in my mind.  i love him,  and he loves me.  he is golden and precious.   the best thing that has ever happened to me.  he takes care of me.  he comforts me.  that's all i need!

title: My Family
author: amber
text: my family is so weird and loud,  but i really am proud.  see we might not be normal,  but who is.   but really can't complain,  cause its all gonna change.  me and my sister just started school,  and its kinda cool.   and we made the volleyball team,  its kinda nerve wrecking.  cause all the girls are talented,  but i guess i fit in.   so thats the story of my family,  we're not normal but very happy.

title: One by one they Lie
author: amber
text: i look through the glass at the water the ice cant pass me by it trickles down my arm one by one they lie the drop does not cease  it leaves me in my wonder why doesn't it stop? the rain the cloud  the thunder but if the little drop gave up what would there be if the drop couldn't go on in the end i wouldn't be me i look up at the sky the cloud shades the sun one by one they lie never think you're done.

title: Midnight breeze
author: amber
text: the midnight breeze cut through me as i walked alone,  like a hot knife through butter.  the cold wind stung my face,   but i continued to walk.  howling wind through the trees mad an erie noise as i walked alone,  and i quickley ran into my house,  as the last of the midnight breeze was lost behind my closed door.
